<item>
            <title>[CXF-6527] WSDLRefValidator reject valid target reference URI/IRI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6527</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a target namespace have &#8220;:&#8221; in the path part of the URI, the validator reject the WSDL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to this piece of code at line 137 of &lt;tt&gt;tools/validator/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/tools/validator/internal/WSDLRefValidator.java&lt;/tt&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; void checkTargetNamespace(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; path) {
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; URL(path).getPath().indexOf(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;:&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) != -1) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ToolException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;: is not a valid &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; in the targetNamespace&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
        }
   } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (MalformedURLException e) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; nothing
&lt;/span&gt;   }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I checked the following specifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xml-names/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;XML namespace&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc3986.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;URI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3987.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;IRI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl20/#Description_targetnamespace_attribute&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;WSDL 2.0 Target namespace&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl#_service&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;WSDL&#160;service definition&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;and nothing forbids having a target namespace like the following one:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://host:port/part/part/resource:resource&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://host:port/part/part/resource:resource&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then the validator add an extra constraint on the WSDL format without any explanation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I looked into the source history, this validation is here since a long period (before going to git), then I was not able to find out the reason behind this explicit check.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could fix this bug or explain why there is a such limitation?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
