                            <comment id="14697302" author="ay" created="Fri, 14 Aug 2015 16:12:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there are some restriction in where &apos;:&apos; can appear in the path part, but I don&apos;t think it is generally forbidden.&lt;br/&gt;
So I am also wondering where this check comes from.&lt;br/&gt;
Depending on what the rules say, I think we can change/update this check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699501" author="ay" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 13:07:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the corresponding code came in as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1200&quot; title=&quot;wsdltojava accepts targetnamespace with &amp;#39;:&amp;#39; in the name but generate code that does not compile&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-1200&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-1200&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is a very old issue supposed to avoid generating an invalid java code.&lt;br/&gt;
It looks like the code generation issue itself does not exist even we omit this check (i.e., allowing a namespace with a colon).&lt;br/&gt;
If it is indeed the case, we can drop/omit this check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14709288" author="ay" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 13:33:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had an irc chat with Dan a couple of days ago and we said we could remove this old restriction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
